HEADWORD: Nee
<hw>Nee</hw> <pr>(n⟦asl⟧)</pr>, <pos>p. p., fem.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
L. <ets>nata</ets>, fem. of <ets>natus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>nasci</ets>
to be born. See <er>Nation</er>.]</ety> <def>Born; -- a term sometimes
used in introducing the name of the family to which a married woman
belongs by birth (i.e. her maiden name); <as>as, Madame de Stael,
<ex>n⟦eacute⟧e</ex> Necker</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

